          Important win for Monaco, it really improves their chances going through. There's no really big teams in this group who would be considered as favorites to win CL but all the teams are very good and there are no easy matches which makes rotating very difficult. Pochettino made a huge mistake not starting Wanyama alongside Dier to give protection, although now on Dembele will start there and his presence will bring Tottenham on a whole new level. With Leverkusen-CSKA ending 2-2 it will surely be great time to watch further matches of this group.

With their first choice XI Spurs would be favorites but rotating too much would be risky. I'd name a strong team here and maybe bring some new faces in against Sunderland next weekend.
